      "id": "w_d363a7e4ad1608_19db01ff652",
      "title": "The Contact",
      "artist": "Barış Tolga Ekinci",
      "year": "2025",
      "description": "The UFO phenomenon and the subject of extraterrestrial life have been examined in many television programs and films within the boundaries of science fiction. On the other hand, especially in recent years, the developments in space technologies and the intense interest of scientists in planets other than Earth have led to the production of many documentaries on ufology. The documentary Contact is the first documentary to address the cases of extraterrestrial life in Anatolia. In the documentary, the historical formation of the contact cases experienced in Turkey is examined in the context of the reality dimension of the ufology phenomenon. The story of the documentary Contact is addressed in a multifaceted manner, from ancient structures in Anatolia to historical events and UFO videos to individual contacts. The documentary Contact is based on the experiences and opinions of distinguished academics, retired officers, archaeologists, art historians, television broadcasters, journalists, UFO researchers, metaphysics experts, and contactees who have had contact with extraterrestrial beings.",
